8. Mediator Pattern
The Goal: Reduce chaotic dependencies between objects. The pattern restricts direct communications between the objects and forces them to collaborate only via a mediator object.
•	How it works: Objects don't talk to each other directly. They send a message to the "Mediator," which then notifies the relevant parties.
•	Real-World Analogy: Air Traffic Control (ATC). Pilots of different planes don't talk to each other to avoid collisions. They all talk to the ATC tower, which coordinates the movement of everyone.
